Solution. Divide the rectangle into two parts by the diagonal line \( a y=b x \) to obtain
\[
\begin{aligned}
\int_{0}^{a} \int_{0}^{b} e^{\max \left\{b^{2} x^{2}, a^{2} y^{2}\right\}} d y d x & =\int_{0}^{a} \int_{0}^{b x / a} e^{b^{2} x^{2}} d y d x+\int_{0}^{b} \int_{0}^{a y / b} e^{a^{2} y^{2}} d x d y \\
& =\int_{0}^{a} \frac{b x}{a} e^{b^{2} x^{2}} d x+\int_{0}^{b} \frac{a y}{b} e^{a^{2} y^{2}} d y \\
& =\int_{0}^{a^{2} b^{2}} \frac{1}{2 a b} e^{u} d u+\int_{0}^{a^{2} b^{2}} \frac{1}{2 a b} e^{v} d v \\
& =\frac{e^{a^{2} b^{2}}-1}{a b}
\end{aligned}
\]

